<p><br />Butler has popular Men's and Women's Basketball teams.&nbsp;The teams train regularly in the Howlands and on the&nbsp;famous MUGA!</p><p>Men's President/Captain: Adam Graver&nbsp; <a href="mailto:adam.graver@durham.ac.uk">adam.graver@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>Women's President: Georgia Palmes <a href="mailto:g.c.palmes@durham.ac.uk">g.c.palmes@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>Women's Captain:&nbsp;Dona Ismaili &nbsp; <a href="mailto:edjona.ismaili@durham.ac.uk">edjona.ismaili@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Links:</span></p><p>Official facebook group:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/281904218594620/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/281904218594620/</a></p><p>Women's facebook group:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/1420640328148742/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/1420640328148742/</a></p><p>Men's facebook group:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/489683251164551/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/489683251164551/</a></p><p>Butler Bball Twitter:&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/ButlerBball24">https://twitter.com/ButlerBball24</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Men's Basketball</span></p><p>With the most improved team competition in the bag, it's time to move on to bigger and better things. Targeting league promotion and a shot at team of the year, this year is going to be the biggest yet for the Men's Team. Whether you've never held a basketball or you've played at the highest level, all are welcome at training sessions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>For more information please contact me on <a href="mailto:adam.graver@durham.ac.uk">adam.graver@durham.ac.uk</a>&nbsp;or come down to training. When we say all are welcome, we really mean ALL ARE WELCOME!</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Women's Basketball</span></p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal">Whether you&rsquo;re a beginner interested in the sport, a netballer turning to the dark side, or a basketball fan keen on serious training, you&rsquo;re most welcome to come along to play for Butler&rsquo;s Women&rsquo;s Basketball team!</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">Newly promoted, we're&nbsp;hoping to recruit lots of&nbsp;freshers (experienced or otherwise) to join us. The more the merrier :D</span></p><p class="MsoNormal">There is no pressure to commit, just come along and have a good time &ndash; who knows, you might pick up some nifty skills along the way!</p><p class="MsoNormal">Training is twice a week: Mondays 6-7pm (Howlands) and mixed training on Wednesdays 5-6pm (Howlands), as well as occasional weekend matches and our famous annual 24 hour Bball!&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal">For more information, send us an email or just turn up to practice!</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal"><img src="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/071.jpg" alt="" /></p><p class="MsoNormal">24 Hour BBall Survivors 2014</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal"><img style="color: black;" src="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/066.jpg" alt="" /></p><p class="MsoNormal">Sports Formal 2012</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<img src="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/017.jpg" alt="" /></p><p class="MsoNormal">Social 2010</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>